Note, however, that each physical SSD is 375GB in size, and no more than 8 drives can be attached to a single instance.

For more information about the effect of this parameter, see https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/instances/specify-min-cpu-platform.

The default value is ``projects/cos-cloud/global/images/family/cos-stable``, which selects the latest stable release of Container-Optimized OS.  This option is provided to allow testing against the beta release of the operating system to ensure that the new version does not interact negatively with production pipelines.  To test a pipeline against the beta release of Container-Optimized OS, use the value ``projects/cos-cloud/global/images/family/cos-beta``.

nvidia_driver_version.description: The NVIDIA driver version to use when attaching an NVIDIA GPU accelerator. docker_cache_images.description: The Compute Engine Disk Images to use as a Docker cache. The disks will be mounted into the Docker folder in a way that the images present in the cache will not need to be pulled. The digests of the cached images must match those of the tags used or the latest version will still be pulled. The root directory of the ext4 image must contain ``image`` and ``overlay2`` directories copied from the Docker directory of a VM where the desired Docker images have already been pulled. Any images pulled that are not cached will be stored on the first cache disk instead of the boot disk. Only a single image is supported.

Specify a unique request ID so that if you must retry your request, the server will know to ignore the request if it has already been completed.
